-- Polish Stocks: KGHM, PBG, PGE, TVN Active in Warsaw Trading
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-03-08T17:01:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/polish-stocks-kghm-polska-miedz-tvn-are-active-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  rose 1.4
percent to 2,296.59 at the close in Warsaw, up for a second day.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
Warsaw Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)  , the copper miner that has
Europe’s biggest output, gained 1.9 percent, the most since Feb.
28, to 146.8 zloty as the metal advanced.  PBG SA (PBG)  , Poland’s third-largest construction
company lost 12 percent to 54 zloty, the lowest level since
October 2005, after announcing a plan to raise capital through a
rights offering or selling convertible bonds.  PGE SA (PGE)   fell 0.9 percent to 19.2 zloty, the lowest
level since Nov. 15, as the country’s largest utility said it
will revise 2011 earnings after a Warsaw court ruled yesterday
to curb compensation for the cancellation of power contracts.  TVN SA (TVN)  , Poland’s biggest television network,
climbed 2.7 percent to 10.85 zloty, gaining for the second day,
after the country’s largest pension fund raised its stake.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
